HEADWORD: Defiant
<hw>De*fi"ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧fiant</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>d⟦eacute⟧fier</ets>. See
<er>Defy</er>.]</ety> <def>Full of defiance; bold; insolent; <as>as, a
<ex>defiant</ex> spirit or act</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In attitude stern and <qex>defiant</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>De*fi"ant*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
